        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1417398142" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18790295102250437">I’d already seen the stage production of ‘Go Back For Murder’ which is an adaptation of this story minus Poirot, so I was already aware of the solution.<br/><br/>It meant that I could enjoy the Belgium detectives inclusion in the original story whilst also appreciating the structure of this novel.<br/><br/>The same events are recounted by the five people who were present that day of a murder sixteen years previous.<br/>I loved how the clues were slowly scattered throughout the story, it’s slightly easier to spot them wh</span>
  <span id="freeText18790295102250437" style="display:none">I’d already seen the stage production of ‘Go Back For Murder’ which is an adaptation of this story minus Poirot, so I was already aware of the solution.<br /><br />It meant that I could enjoy the Belgium detectives inclusion in the original story whilst also appreciating the structure of this novel.<br /><br />The same events are recounted by the five people who were present that day of a murder sixteen years previous.<br />I loved how the clues were slowly scattered throughout the story, it’s slightly easier to spot them when your able to look for them!<br /><br />Any entry that includes Poirot is always going to be enjoyable, but it’s to the novels strength that the other characters are so interesting and compelling.<br />It can be difficult to re-read a mystery novel once you know the solution, but this isn’t one of them mainly due to the supporting Five Little Pigs.</span>
